## Development

### Available Commands

- `just init` - Initialize development environment
- `just run` - Run the main application
- `just destroy` - Remove build artifacts
- `just help` - Show available commands

### Code Quality

- `just code-format` - Auto-fix code formatting (clang-format)
- `just code-style` - Check code style (clang-tidy)
- `just code-typecheck` - Run static analysis (cppcheck)
- `just code-security` - Run security checks (flawfinder)
- `just code-deptry` - Check include hygiene (IWYU, advisory)
- `just code-spell` - Check spelling
- `just code-semgrep` - Run custom static analysis

### Testing

- `just test` - Run unit tests
- `just test-coverage` - Run tests with coverage ({{coverage_threshold}}% threshold)
- `just code-sanitize` - Run tests with AddressSanitizer + UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer

### CI

- `just ci` - Run all validation checks (verbose)
- `just ci-quiet` - Run all checks (silent, fail-fast)

The CI pipeline runs the following steps in order:
1. `init` - Initialize environment
2. `code-format` - Auto-format code
3. `code-style` - Check code style (clang-tidy)
4. `code-typecheck` - Static analysis (cppcheck)
5. `code-security` - Security scan (flawfinder)
6. `code-deptry` - Include hygiene (IWYU)
7. `code-spell` - Spell checking
8. `code-semgrep` - Custom static analysis
9. `test` - Unit tests
10. `code-sanitize` - Sanitizer tests

